    "Lawrence 2012; Lawther et al. 2023).",
    "All in all, our theoretical understanding of accretion discs is under tension.",
    "On the one hand, theoretical developments indicate that the accretion disc should not be universally described by a thin-disc model.",
    "On the other hand, the thin-disc cannot explain all the observations: the size is found to be larger than expected but its dependence on wavelength follows the R ∝ λ 4/3 relation from the standard model."
